MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector applying knowledge of established transportation or traffic management rules to preform a full range of transportation support duties. Examples of specialized experience includes: 1) Determine shipping methods for personal property of clients;
2) Secure carriers to arrange for pickup or delivery of freight shipments;
3) Report discrepancies to prevent or minimize loss, damages, or hardships for customers.
4) Advise individuals of their entitlements or responsibilities for shipment, storage, processing claims, or quality control data.. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
